-- Smer Party Wins Most Votes in Slovakia’s Snap Election, Exit Polls Show
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k   a n d   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2012-03-10T21:16:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-10/smer-party-wins-most-votes-in-slovakia-s-snap-election-exit-polls-show.html
Slovakia’s Smer party, led by ex-
Premier  Robert Fico , won the most votes in snap elections today
on pledges to tax higher earners and companies, two exit polls
showed.  Smer received 39.6 percent of the votes, followed by the
 Christian Democrats  with 9.9 percent, according to an exit poll
by the private company Focus for public Slovak Television. Smer
had 37.3 percent of votes in a separate survey conducted by the
MVK company for private Markiza television.  The Focus poll gave Smer 75 of parliament’s 150 seats,
while the MVK survey put Smer at 69 seats.  To contact the reporter on this story:
